President Roh Moo-Hyun called Monday for a probe into allegations that intelligence officials had illegally taped conversations between South Korea 's ambassador to the United States and a Samsung Group executive .A former NIS official who headed a wiretapping team was arrested Thursday for leaking the taped 1997 conversation between Hong Seok-Hyun , a brother-in-law of Samsung Group chief Lee Kun-Hee , and a top official of the group .Kim Dae-Jung beat Lee in a presidential election in late 1997 .Kim said there had been no illicit wiretapping under the government of President Roh Moo-Hyun .